Personal details of 2,379 US Marines stationed in the Persian Gulf have been released by the Handala hacker group, which claims the leak is "just a drop in the ocean."

The group warns it has extensive data on US military personnel, including identities, movements, and more.

Handala also claims to have sent direct WhatsApp messages to Marines, urging them to say their final goodbyes.

